Each time a remainder a is found, it's added to r the number of times this remainder has been seen before. Then, m[a] is incremented. So the code is effectively counting the number of pairs (i,j) where the substring ending at position i and j have the same remainder. So the total count is the number of such pairs. In the example "2019", the code returns r=3. Hmm, but I'm getting a bit stuck. Let's proceed to code. So in C, the code would be:

